<paragraph id="8B888D405A27FF889FF803ECE68C08A4" blockId="10.[189,1398,1955,2017]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
The specific epithet is the feminine participle of the Latin verb â 
<emphasis id="B94351525A27FF889CFC03ECE15108F8" box="[953,1062,1955,1981]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">confundo</emphasis>
â, meaning âto confuseâ, and refers to the fact that this species has been confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C37F6C35A27FF889C1A0388E68308A5" box="[863,1012,1990,2017]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Astiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="delicatula">
<emphasis id="B94351525A27FF889C1A0388E68308A5" box="[863,1012,1990,2017]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">A. delicatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
