<subSubSection id="C32DDECB5A21FF8E9FF8058EE7F90B25" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B888D405A21FF8E9FF8058EE4390E9E" blockId="12.[189,334,449,475]" box="[189,334,449,475]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading id="D0C03A2C5A21FF8E9FF8058EE4390E9E" bold="true" box="[189,334,449,475]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B94351525A21FF8E9FF8058EE4390E9E" bold="true" box="[189,334,449,475]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B888D405A21FF8E9FF805BFE7F90B25" blockId="12.[189,1399,496,1120]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Herb, up to 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9E0B05BFE4EE0D4F" box="[334,409,496,522]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="cm" value="60.0">60 cm</quantity>
tall; stems quadrangular in cross section, glabrous. Stipule base 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9BE505BFE0450D4F" box="[1184,1330,496,523]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5â1.5 mm</quantity>
long, pubescent; fimbriae usually bifid, 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9D1C065CE79A0D68" box="[601,749,531,557]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.8" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.4">0.4â1.2 mm</quantity>
long, colleter-tipped. Leaves sessile; blades narrowly elliptic, 2.5â20 Ã 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9ECD0679E76D0D14" box="[392,538,566,593]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="2.35" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="0.5">0.5â4.2mm</quantity>
, glabrous or scabrate, darker green above, paler green below; base attenuate; apex acute; margin revolute when dry; midvein prominent or invisible above, always prominent below; secondary veins invisible or 1â2 on each side of the midvein; intersecondaries invisible. Inflorescences terminal, compound dichasia, several-flowered; peduncle 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9C2806EFE6950DFF" box="[877,994,672,698]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="0.0">0â12 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous. Pedicels (0.7â) 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9A1C06EFE46D0D98" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="9.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="6.25" valueMax="9.5" valueMin="3.0">3â 9.5 mm</quantity>
long, scabrate. Flowers probably heterostylous (only flowers with anthers exserted and style included were observed). Calyx green; tube reduced; lobes 4, triangular, 0.7â1 Ã 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9B3506A9E0710C44" box="[1136,1286,742,769]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.5" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.4">0.4â0.6 mm</quantity>
, glabrous to scabrate. Corolla white; tube funnel-shaped, 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9DA40746E6070C61" box="[737,880,777,804]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.5">1.5â1.7 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous outside and pubescent inside; lobes 4, ovate, 1.5â1.6 Ã 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9EA90762E71C0C02" box="[492,619,813,839]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.9" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.8">0.8â1 mm</quantity>
, glabrous. Stamens inserted near the base of the corolla lobes and exserted for ca 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9E35071FE4C30C2F" box="[368,436,848,874]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
beyond the corolla throat. Anthers ellipsoid, 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9C86071FE14A0C2F" box="[963,1085,848,874]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.9" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.8">0.8â1 mm</quantity>
long; filaments dorsifixed, 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9FF8073CE4390CC8" box="[189,334,883,909]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5499999999999998" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="1.5499999999999998" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.4">1.4â1.7 mm</quantity>
long. Pollen tricolporate. Ovary 2-locular, broadly obovoid to broadly depressed obovoid, 0.5â0.7 Ã 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9E0607D9E4B50CF4" box="[323,450,918,945]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.85" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.7">0.7â1 mm</quantity>
, glabrous; placenta attached near the middle of the septum, stalked, globose, bearing few (3â4) ovules per locule. Style 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9DFC07F6E63E0C91" box="[697,841,953,980]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2â1.3 mm</quantity>
long, included, glabrous; stigma bilobed, lobes 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9FF80792E4240CB2" box="[189,339,989,1015]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3â0.4 mm</quantity>
long, papillate to hirtellous. Capsules broadly depressed obovoid, well-developed beak, 1.2â1.4 Ã 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9E70004FE4BC0B5F" box="[309,459,1024,1050]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.3">2.3â2.7 mm</quantity>
, crowned with the persistent calyx lobes, glabrous, dehiscence loculicidal. Seeds few (2â3), elliptic in outline, ventral groove present, 0.8â1 Ã 
<quantity id="4CCF20A55A21FF8E9CF5006CE13E0B78" box="[944,1097,1059,1085]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.6">0.6â0.8 mm</quantity>
, black; seed coat surface reticulate, microsculpturing favulariate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32DDECB5A21FF8E9FF800C8E6950B95" box="[189,994,1159,1232]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B888D405A21FF8E9FF800C8E4210BE4" blockId="12.[189,342,1159,1185]" box="[189,342,1159,1185]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
